channel.title: Ask a Homosexual
channel.description:
No one has done it yet... I think I may be one of, if not the only one here judging from the makeup of the other debate thread... So really, if only for curiosity's sake, ask me whatever you wish.
[b]Answered by me:[/b] [quote] Do homosexuals answer questions on their thread? So far I've seen no evidence of this [/quote] I just got back from school/public drunken-ness. [quote] Do you liek mudkipz? [/quote] Yes. [quote] Do you dress in leather tongues and hump random people on the street because you like the attention? [/quote] No, but I do hit on people when I'm brazenly inebriated. I'd suppose the gay attention whore is a negative stereotype. [quote] Do gay people prefer mac OS? Because I've been calling apple users faggots for years and it would suck if I was wrong... [/quote] I certainly don't. [quote] Do you get a whole lot of pointless abuse by people on the internet who abuse you mainly because it's the internet and you can't do shit here? [/quote] Slightly. Though no more than in real life, and I usually respond with something witty and equally as hateful. [quote] How is it like to be gay ? Would you prefer being straight ? [/quote] I don't really know anything else. I suppose it would be easier to be straight, and kind of nice, but at the same time I wouldn't be me if I were straight, I'd be someone completely different with different experiences. I wish people would accept it as if I were straight though. It's annoying, because while a lot of people would say "Don't push your sexuality on me" I tend to have to deal with heterosexuals rubbing it in my face every waking moment. The general malaise and loneliness are actually pretty difficult to deal with. [quote] If it's all about arse, why don't gays like a little bit of tit?
What I mean to say is, despite the fact you are homosexual, are you still attracted to women's cleavage? [/quote] Women are quite pretty, actually. They're really, really, really good looking, I like to look at women. But I have to urge to stick my stuff into a muff, if that's what you're asking. And before you ask, no, I don't like traps. [quote] Do you love mangina? I must say, I'm a fan. [/quote] See above. [quote] Does having a dick in your butt feel kinda like pooping in and out really fast?
Also last time I remember you said you were bi. Are you gay now or still going both ways? [/quote] Not really. It's kind of like the feeling you get of an orgasm, but inside you, and about twice as strong, over and over again. Then the end of it is just glorious. And no, I'm about 99% gay at this point. [quote] My girlfriend told me that semen tastes best when the man has had a diet of strawberries and pineapple since one day before his ejaculation. Is this true?
She also said that alcohol, grilled and smoked meat and tobacco have the exact opposite effect, making it taste more and more disgusting the more they were consumed before. [/quote] To my knowledge, it does. At least, I thought so... >_> [quote] Do you feel that you have a choice to be gay or not? [/quote] No, I don't. I like guys in the exact same way straight people are attracted to the opposite sex; I don't see anyone asking them if it's a choice. [quote] I'm surprised no one has asked you this. Do you find it offensive when people use the term faggot/fag to mean something other than a gay person? (or even to mean a gay person, I guess) [/quote] The word itself doesn't piss me off, it's the attitude of intolerance and douche-ness that comes attached to it. [quote] What is your favorite kind of birthday cake? Also, pepsi or coke, those being your only two choices?
If you were trapped on a desert island, and you could make any song into a person to hang out with, what song would you choose? [/quote] Vanilla/Caramel Ice Cream Cake. Pepsi. Calliope by The Veils or I Love Death by Lodger. [quote] Hey FAG how does DICKS feel in your ASS Also when did you realize you liked the same sex? [/quote] Feels good man. I figured it out at about 13. [quote] Did it just hit or was it gradual? [/quote] It kinda hit me, actually. But "the gay" gets more intense over time, trust me.
